    <h1>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h1>

<div class="content">

<div class="text">
  <ul>
<li><a href="#1"><strong>Why should I give to UC Irvine?</strong></a></li>
<li><a href="#2">I'm not comfortable giving online. Is it really safe?</a></li>
<li><a href="#5">Can I make my donation anonymous?</a></li>
<li><a href="#6">I can't find the fund I want to donate to by searching, what do I do?</a></li>
<li><a href="#7">Is my gift tax deductible?</a></li>
<li><a href="#8">Will I get a receipt for tax purposes?</a></li>
<li><a href="#9">What is UC Irvine's Tax ID number?</a></li>
<li><a href="#10">How do I update my personal information with UC Irvine?</a></li>
<li><a href="#11">Whom can I contact for more information on how to make a gift?</a></li>
<li><a href="/ways/disclosure.php">UCI and the UCI Foundation Disclosure Statements for Donors</a></li>
</ul>
<h2>Why should I give to UC Irvine?</h2>
<p>Because UC Irvine only receives a fraction of its total annual budget from state funding&#8212;<strong>just 11%</strong> &#8212;philanthropic contributions are critical to the university&#8217;s continued success. This campus depends on private support so that it can continue to deliver the local impact, national influence and global reach UC Irvine has achieved as the region&#8217;s leading research university.</p>
<p>[<a href="#top">top of page</a>]</p>
<h2>I'm not comfortable giving online. Is it really safe?</h2>
<p>The UC Irvine Foundation uses industry-standard SSL (Secure Sockets Layer) encryption to protect the confidentiality of your personal information. Read our <a href="http://www.uci.edu/privacy.php" target="_blank">privacy policy</a> for more information.</p>
<p class="headline"><strong>If you prefer to give your gift via check:</strong></p>
<p><a href="/ways/index.php#check">Give via check</a></p>
<p>[<a href="#top">top of page</a>]</p>
<p><a id="5" name="5"></a></p>
<h2>Can I make my donation anonymous?</h2>
<p>You will need to provide your personal information so that you can be credited for the gift. However, if you want your gift to be acknowledged as anonymous, please note this in the &#8220;Comments&#8221; section.</p>
<p>[<a href="#top">top of page</a>]</p>
<p><a id="6" name="6"></a></p>
<h2>I can't find the fund I want to donate to by searching, what do I do?</h2>
<p>At the present time, only UCI Foundation funds are available through eGiving. You can still make a donation to your fund by completing and sending in a gift form. In the &#8220;Comments&#8221; section, provide as much information as you can about the gift you are trying to make. A University representative will contact you if they cannot determine a proper match.</p>
<p>[<a href="#top">top of page</a>]</p>
<p><a id="7" name="7"></a></p>
<h2>Is my gift tax deductible?</h2>
<p>The UC Irvine Foundation is a nonprofit 501(c)(3) corporation. Your gift qualifies for tax-deduction in accordance with IRS regulations during the calendar year that you make your gift. Consult your tax professional for more information.</p>
<p>[<a href="#top">top of page</a>]</p>
<p><a id="8" name="8"></a></p>
<h2>Will I get a receipt for tax purposes?</h2>
<p>If your donation qualifies as a charitable contribution, a gift receipt for your financial records will be sent to you in the mail.</p>
<p>[<a href="#top">top of page</a>]</p>
<p><a id="9" name="9"></a></p>
<h2>What is UC Irvine's Tax ID number?</h2>
<p>The ID number for gifts to the <strong>UC Irvine Foundation</strong> is <span class="giftTotal">95-2540117</span>.</p>
<p>[<a href="#top">top of page</a>]</p>
<p><a id="10" name="10"></a></p>
<h2>How do I update my personal information with UC Irvine?</h2>
<p>To let us know of changes in address, marital status, etc., please send an e-mail to our Alumni Records unit at <a href="mailto:alumni@uci.edu">alumni@uci.edu</a>.</p>
<p>[<a href="#top">top of page</a>]</p>
<p><a id="11" name="11"></a></p>
<h2>Whom can I contact for more information on how to make a gift?</h2>
<p>Please call 949-824-0142 or email us at <a href="mailto:annualfund@uci.edu">annualfund@uci.edu</a> and we&#8217;ll be happy to answer your questions.</p>
<p>[<a href="#top">top of page</a>] <a id="disclosure" name="disclosure"></a></p>
</div>
  
